.\" Manpage for simple_shell
.TH SIMPLE_SHELL 1 "2025-11-08" "1.0" "Simple Shell Manual"
.SH NAME
simple_shell \- a minimal Unix command-line interpreter
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B simple_shell
.RI [ command ... ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
simple_shell is a basic shell written in C that executes commands read from the standard input. 
It supports:
.IP "\- Executing commands"
Runs external commands with arguments.

.IP "\- Built-in commands"
Currently supports:
.RS
.TP
.B exit
Exit the shell.
.TP
.B env
Prints the environment variables.
.RE

.IP "\- Command chaining"
Supports execution of multiple commands separated by \";\".

.SH USAGE
Run the shell by executing:
.RS
$ ./simple_shell
.RE

Type commands as you would in a normal shell. To exit, type:
.RS
$ exit
.RE

